Write a program to demonstrate set operations (union, intersection, difference, and symmetric difference) between a set of prime numbers and a set of odd numbers up to a given limit.

SOLUTION:

limit=10
prime={num for num in range (2,limit+1)if all(num%i=0 for i in range(2,int(num**0.5)+1))}
odd={num for num in range(1,limit+1)if num%2!=0}
print("prime nos",prime)
print("odd nos",odd)
union=prime|odd
print("union",union)
intersection=prime&odd
print("intersection",intersection)
difference=prime-odd
print("difference",difference)
sym difference=prime^odd
print("symmetrical difference",sym difference)
